items.title: India could benefit from free trade in long term: Mercedes-Benz India MD & CEO
items.description: In FY25, the overall luxury car segment is estimated to be at over 51,500 units compared to about 49,800 units in FY24.

items.title: Apple India produces $22 billion of iPhones in shift from China
items.description: The ramp-up suggests the iPhone maker and its suppliers are accelerating a pivot to India from China, a process it began when harsh Covid lockdowns hurt production at Apple’s largest plant.

items.title: TCS CEO warns of tariff fallout on retail, travel, and auto sectors amid trade uncertainty
items.description: However, the banking and financial services sector, which accounts for nearly a third of TCS's revenue, remains largely unaffected by the trade tensions, according to Krithivasan.

items.title: Aurobindo Pharma bags USFDA nod for generic Xarelto, eyes $447 million US market
items.description: In addition to the final approval for the 2.5mg dosage, Aurobindo has also secured tentative approvals from the USFDA for Rivaroxaban tablets in 10mg, 15mg, and 20mg strengths.
